International travel
Commercial flights to and from Morocco remain very limited. Check with your travel company for the latest information.
Entry and borders
See Entry requirements to find out what you will need to do when you arrive in Morocco.
Travel in Morocco
State of Health Emergency
On 9 July, the Moroccan Government announced a further extension to the State of Health Emergency until 10 August, along with details of its strategy for easing restrictive measures. The strategy, which came into effect from 11 June, categorises provinces/prefectures in Morocco into two zones according to the pandemic situation in each province/prefecture. The wearing of face masks in public spaces remains mandatory.
The Moroccan authorities review the categorisation of prefectures/provinces on a weekly basis.
Below is the latest list of areas for which movement restrictions are in place:
Zone 1
  Prefecture and provinces of the Oriental Prefecture of M’diq-Fnideq Province of Taza    
  Provinces of the Beni Mellal-Khenifra region Province of Tetouan Province of Khemisset    
  Provinces of the Draa-Tafilalet region Province of Fahs-Anjra Sidi Kacem Province    
  Prefectures and provinces of the Souss-Massa region Province of Al-Hoceima Province of Sidi Slimane    
  Province of Chefchaouen Province of Sidi Slimane Province of Ouezzane    
  Province of Settat Prefecture of Meknes Province of Sidi Bennour    
  Ifrane Province Chichaoua Province Province of Al-Haouz    
  Province of Moulay Yaacoub Province of Kelaa of Sraghna Province of Sefrou    
